prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF  SOLID STATE PHASED ARRAY RADAR SYSTEM (SSPARS) PROGRAM IS COMPRISED OF FIVE RADAR SITES AT THE FOLLOWING 21ST SPACE WING (21 SW) GEOGRAPHICALLY-SEPARATED UNITS (GSUS) IN THE NORTHERN HEMISPHERE: 7TH SPACE WARNING SQUADRON (7 SWS) AT BEALE AIR FORCE BASE (AFB) CALIFORNIA (CA); 6 SWS AT CAPE COD AIR FORCE STATION (AFS) MASSACHUSETTS (MA); 13/213 SWS AT CLEAR AFS ALASKA (AK); ROYAL AIR FORCE (RAF) FYLINGDALES, UNITED KINGDOM (UK); AND 12 SWS AT THULE AIR BASE (AB) GREENLAND (GL). PROVIDE ALL NON-PERSONAL SERVICES, ADMINISTRATIVE, FINANCIAL, AND MANAGERIAL RESOURCES NECESSARY ON A CONTINUOUS 24-HOURS-A-DAY, 7-DAYS-A-WEEK (24/7) BASIS TO SUPPORT THE FIVE SSPARS INSTALLATIONS/SITES IN THE FOLLOWING MISSIONS AND SERVICES AREAS: RADAR OPERATIONS SUPPORT, RADAR MAINTENANCE, MISSION COMPUTER MAINTENANCE, TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE, EXERCISES AND TESTING SUPPORT, SIMULATION TRAINERS, TRAINING DEVELOPMENT AND SUPPORT, MILITARY SATELLITE COMMUNICATIONS, COMMUNICATIONS-ELECTRONICS, ELECTRONIC SYSTEM MANAGEMENT, SUPPLY, FUELS, NON-CLASSIFIED INTERNET PROTOCOL ROUTER NETWORK (NIPRNET), SECRET INTERNET PROTOCOL ROUTER NETWORK (SIPRNET), ENVIRONMENTAL, OCCUPATIONAL HEALTH, MEDICAL AND PUBLIC HEALTH, CIVIL ENGINEERING, VEHICLE AND TRAFFIC MANAGEMENT, SERVICES (FOOD AND MORALE/WELFARE ACTIVITIES), INDUSTRIAL, PHYSICAL AND OPERATIONAL SECURITY, INFORMATION MANAGEMENT, AND TRANSITION (PHASE-IN/OUT) ACTIVITIES. INCLUDES SECURITY CLASSIFICATION UP TO TOP SECRET (TS)/SENSITIVE COMPARTMENTED INFORMATION (SCI) LEVEL IN SUPPORT OF SITE SENSITIVE COMPARTMENTALIZED INFORMATION FACILITY (SCIF) AND COMMUNICATIONS REQUIREMENTS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF  SBIR PHASE II - LIVE VIRTUAL CONSTRUCTIVE AND GAME   ASSISTED EXPERIMENTAL DESIGN II (LVC&G-AED): THE PURPOSE OF THE LVC&G-AED SBIR PHASE II EFFORT IS TO DEVELOP A DECISION-SUPPORT SYSTEM THAT WILL GUIDE INDIVIDUALS THROUGH A TEN STEP RESEARCH PROCESS FROM DEFINING THE RESEARCH QUESTION, CHOOSING VARIABLES OF INTEREST, AND DEVELOPING RELEVANT MEASURES. THIS PROCESS IS BOTH SUFFICIENTLY HIGH-LEVEL TO CAPTURE THE QUESTIONS OF THE VARIOUS PROFESSIONALS INVOLVED IN SIMULATION DEVELOPMENT, YET SUFFICIENTLY RIGOROUS TO ENSURE THAT SPECIFIC RESEARCH QUESTIONS ARE ADDRESSED.  CURRENTLY THERE ARE NO SYSTEMATIC METHODS FOR ASSEMBLING ENVIRONMENTS AND DESIGNING EXPERIMENTS OR TRAINING FROM THESE MULTIPLE PERSPECTIVES, FROM SIMULATOR PROGRAMMERS TO SUBJECT MATTER EXPERTS.  THE FOCUS OF THE PHASE II EFFORT IS TO BUILD A WORKING PROTOTYPE OF THE ASSISTED EXPERIMENTAL DESIGNER (AED) TOOL, INCLUDING THE USER INTERFACE, UNDERLYING EXPLORATION AND OPTIMIZATION MODEL, AND KNOWLEDGE DATABASE. THIS PROTOTYPE WILL BE DEMONSTRATED TO BE USABLE BY ANY INDIVIDUAL, REGARDLESS OF BACKGROUND, ENABLING THEM TO QUICKLY AND EFFICIENTLY CREATE SCIENTIFICALLY VALID EXPERIMENTAL SCENARIOS, SAVING MANPOWER, TIME, AND FINANCIAL RESOURCES.

TO ASSIST THE COE-DMHA AND VPA IN THE EVALUATION OF PROGRAM EFFECTIVENESS AND IN THE ASSESSMENT OF PROGRAM IMPACT BY PEPFAR INDICATORS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF  THE E-COMMERCE OPERATIONAL SYSTEMS SUPPORT (EOSS) CONTRACT WILL ACQUIRE INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (IT) SUPPORT SERVICES TO PERFORM SUSTAINMENT ENGINEERING, ENHANCEMENT ENGINEERING, AND ENGINEERING MANAGEMENT OF THE TRICARE MANAGEMENT ACTIVITY (TMA) E-COMMERCE SOFTWARE APPLICATIONS TO INCLUDE: THE ORACLE FEDERAL FINANCIALS (OFF) COMMERCIAL OFF-THE-SHELF (COTS)ACCOUNTING SYSTEM WITH CUSTOM EXTENSIONS, THE E-COMMERCE DATA WAREHOUSE (EDW) WITH DATA MARTS, THE CUSTOM-BUILT MANAGEMENT TRACKING AND REPORTING (MTR) AND EXTRANET APPLICATIONS, THE COMMERCIAL-OFF-THE-SHELF (COTS) PRISM APPLICATION, AND THE DOCUMENTUM APPLICATION WITH CUSTOM EXTENSIONS.  THE EOSS CONTRACT WILL PROVIDE: (1) MAINTENANCE OF EXISTING CUSTOM E-COMMERCE SOFTWARE; (2) MAINTENANCE OF EXISTING COTS EXTENSIONS AND CONFIGURATIONS; (3) CORRECTIVE SOFTWARE MAINTENANCE, INCLUDING ALL EFFORTS TO DIAGNOSE AND CORRECT PROCESSING OR PERFORMANCE ERRORS; AND (4) COORDINATION FOR AND TROUBLESHOOTING OF REMOTE DEFENSE INFORMATION SYSTEMS AGENCY (DISA) COMPUTING AND NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE CAPABILITIES. EOSS CONTRACT PERSONNEL WILL CONDUCT REGULARLY SCHEDULED SOFTWARE ADJUSTMENTS AND INSPECTIONS, UPGRADES AND MAJOR REPAIRS OF APPLICATION COMPONENTS, PREVENTIVE SOFTWARE MAINTENANCE TASKS, REGULARLY SCHEDULED OPERATIONAL TASKS, AND BREAK-FIX EMERGENCY RESPONSE.  IN ADDITION, THE EOSS CONTRACT WILL PROVIDE: (1) MODIFICATIONS TO EXISTING OPERATIONAL CUSTOM SOFTWARE AND COTS EXTENSIONS; (2) EXPANSION OF EXISTING CAPABILITIES TO NEW USERS; AND (3) APPLICATION CHANGES MANDATED BY LAWS AND DIRECTIVES.   FINALLY, THE EOSS CONTRACT WILL ALSO SERVE AS A VEHICLE TO IMPLEMENT E-COMMERCE MODERNIZATION PROJECTS TO INCLUDE DISA INFRASTRUCTURE AND NETWORK PLANNING.   IN CONDUCTING THESE ACTIVITIES, EOSS IT SUPPORT PERSONNEL WILL PERFORM SOFTWARE AND SYSTEMS ENGINEERING, BUSINESS ANALYSIS, SOFTWARE DESIGN, DEVELOPMENT AND INTEGRATION, COTS SOFTWARE CONFIGURATION AND MANAGEMENT, TESTING (INTEGRATION, UNIT, SYSTEM, AND USER ACCEPTANCE), DOCUMENTATION MAINTENANCE, SOFTWARE DEPLOYMENT, SOFTWARE OPERATIONS, AND APPLICATION TRAINING.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: CONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE A BROAD RANGE OF SPECIALIZED AND PROFESSIONAL, PROGRAM MANAGEMENT SUPPORT FOR AIR FORCE CIVIL ENGINEERING INSTALLATION MANAGEMENT PROGRAMS AND INITIATIVES. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL MANAGE, PLAN, ORGANIZE, PROGRAM, AND ADMINISTER AF REAL PROPERTY ASSETS AND SIMILARLY PLAN, ANALYZE, BUDGET, AND PROGRAM REQUIREMENTS USING FACILITY COST MODELING AND/OR OTHER COMMERCIAL ALGORITHMS FOR INSTALLATION SUPPORT PROGRAMS. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL PLAN, COORDINATE, AND DEVELOP NECESSARY POLICIES, PROCEDURES AND REPORTING. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL ASSIST IN IDENTIFYING, ANALYZING, AND VALIDATING AF FACILITY INVESTMENTS AND INSTALLATION SERVICES USING DOD MODELS OR AF ALGORITHMS DESIGNED TO STANDARDIZE INVESTMENTS ACROSS THE SERVICES THROUGH THE POM PROCESS. CONTRACTOR WILL ASSIST IN DETERMINING THE AF PLANT REPLACEMENT VALUE (PRV), MANAGE FACILITY FORECASTS, FACILITY CONDITION (Q-RATING) AND UTILIZATION RATINGS (U-RATING). THE CONTRACTOR WILL EMPLOY A VARIETY OF MODELS SUCH AS THE FACILITY SUSTAINMENT MODEL (FSM), FACILITY OPERATIONS MODEL (FOM), FACILITIES INVESTMENT METRIC (FIM) AND OTHERS. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL INTERFACE WITH FACILITY OPERATIONS AND FACILITY INVESTMENT PROGRAMS AND DEVELOP BASE OPERATING SUPPORT/INSTALLATION SERVICES PROGRAMS. THE CONTRACTOR WILL ASSIST IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF DOD S INSTALLATION SERVICES MODEL (ISM). THE CONTRACTOR WILL DEVELOP AND MANAGE POLICY AND PROCEDURES AND ASSURE ACCOUNTABILITY FOR AF REAL PROPERTY INVENTORY AND SUPPORT STRATEGY AND THE AIR FORCE S PLAN TO MEET DOD S FINANCIAL IMPROVEMENT AND AUDIT READINESS (FIAR) PLAN. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL ASSIST IN DEVELOPING, VALIDATING, AND ANALYZING DATA SUPPORTING THE COMMON DELIVERY OF INSTALLATION SUPPORT (CDIS). THE CONTRACTOR SHALL ALSO ASSIST IN WRITING, COORDINATING, SCHEDULING, AND BRIEFING CORRESPONDENCE AND OTHER COMMUNICATIONS REGARDING VARIOUS INSTALLATION MANAGEMENT INITIATIVES.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: RECOVERYPROJECT#::30947::RP# REPAIR HVAC - TRAINING BARRACKS.  THE UTILITY COMPANY AND THEIR COMPETING SUBCONTRACTORS WILL MAKE ARRANGEMENTS FOR QUALIFIED CONTRACTORS TO PROVIDE NECESSARY MECHANICAL, ELECTRICAL AND GENERAL CONSTRUCTION CONTRACT WORK TO REMOVE AND REPLACE COMPONENTS OF BUILDING LIGHTING AND HVAC MECHANICAL SYSTEMS WHICH WILL RESULT IN ENERGY EFFICIENT SAVINGS OF ELECTRICAL, NATURAL GAS AND OPERATIONAL. RECOVERY-PER FAR 5.7 THIS NOTICE IS PROVIDED FOR INFORMATION PURPOSES ONLY; THEREFORE FAR 5.203 DOES NOT APPLY. THIS OPPORTUNITY WAS AVAILABLE ONLY TO CONTRACTOR(S) UNDER THE CURRENT CONTRACT. SOUTH ALABAMA ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE (SEAC) (UTILITY) (DUNS 007961295) AND THEIR COMPETING SUBCONTRACTORS PERFORM UNDER THE PRE-EXISTING UTILITY ENERGY SAVINGS CONTRACT (UESC) AGREEMENT AND PREVIOUSLY ESTABLISHED INDEFINITE DELIVERY-INDEFINITE QUANTITY TYPE CONTRACTING VEHICLE W9124G-05-D-0007.  THIS CONTRACT ACTION WAS ACCOMPLISHED USING OTHER THAN COMPETITIVE PROCEDURES BECAUSE A STATUTE EXISTS THAT EXPRESSLY AUTHORIZES OR REQUIRES THAT THE ACQUISITION BE MADE FROM A SPECIFIC SOURCE OR THROUGH ANOTHER AGENCY (FAR 6.302-5); PER FAR 6.302-5 A J&A IS NOT REQUIRED FOR THIS AWARD.  THIS CONTRACT ACTION WAS ACCOMPLISHED USING OTHER THAN COMPETITIVE PROCEDURES BECAUSE THIS IS AN ORDER UNDER AN EXISTING CONTRACT THAT WAS AWARDED USING NON-COMPETITIVE PROCEDURES.  PROJECTS ISSUED UNDER THIS UESC AGREEMENT WILL PRODUCE FINANCIAL SAVINGS TO THE GOVERNMENT THAT ARE EQUAL OR GREATER THAN THE COST OF IMPLEMENTING THE ENERGY CONSERVATION PROJECT (ECP).  THE AMOUNT OF THE INVESTMENT WILL GENERATE SAVINGS TO PAY FOR THE PROJECT OVER A SPECIFIED PAYBACK PERIOD.  THE UTILITY COMPANY AND THEIR SUBCONTRACTORS PERFORM COMPETITIVE BIDDING AMONG CONTRACTORS TO ESTABLISH FIRM FIXED PRICE PROJECTS AND ARE SUBMITTED AND PROPOSED TO FORT RUCKER TECHNICAL PERSONNEL FOR REVIEW AND ANALYSIS. A UESC IS ONE VEHICLE THAT A FEDERAL AGENCY AND ITS UTILITY COMPANY CAN USE TO IMPLEMENT ENERGY EFFICIENCY, WATER CONSERVATION AND RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECTS.
